st:lc: _O Come_
l:b:O come, let us sing unto the Lord; *
l:b:i: let us heartily rejoice in the strength of our salvation.
l:b:Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving *
l:b:i: and show ourselves glad in him with psalms.
l:b:For the Lord is a great God *
l:b:i: and a great King above all gods.
l:b:In his hand are all the depths of the earth, *
l:b:i: and the heights of the hills are his also.
l:b:The sea is his, for he made it, *
l:b:i: and his hands prepared the dry land.
l:b:O come, let us worship and fall down, *
