st:lc: _We Praise You, O God_
l:b:We praise you, O God; we acclaim you as Lord; *
l:b:i: all creation worships you, the Father everlasting.
l:b:To you all angels, all the powers of heaven, *
l:b:i: the cherubim and seraphim, sing in endless praise:
l:b:Holy, Holy, Holy, Lord God of power and might, *
l:b:i: heaven and earth are full of your glory.
l:b:The glorious company of apostles praise you. *
l:b:i: The noble fellowship of prophets praise you.
l:b:The white-robed army of martyrs praise you. *
l:b:i: Throughout the world the holy Church acclaims you:
l:b:Father, of majesty unbounded,
l:b:your true and only Son, worthy of all praise, *
l:b:i: and the Holy Spirit, advocate and guide.
l:b:You, Christ, are the king of glory, *
l:b:i:the eternal Son of the Father.
l:b: When you took our flesh to set us free *
l:b:i:you humbly chose the Virgin's womb.
l:b: You overcame the sting of death *
l:b:i:and opened the kingdom of heaven to all believers.
l:b: You are seated at God's right hand in glory. *
l:b:i:We believe that you will come to be our judge.
l:b: Come then, Lord, and help your people, *
l:b:i:bought with the price of your own blood,
l:b: and bring us with your saints *
l:b:i:to glory everlasting.
