tb: The Confession and Apostles' Creed may be omitted, provided each is said at least once during the course of the day.
tb: The Gloria Patri (Glory be...) in the opening versicles may be said in unison. The following form of the Gloria Patri may alternatively be used:
l:b:Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit:
l:b:i: As it was in the beginning, is now, and will be for ever. Amen.
